  CLOCK.SYS [ON|OFF]

This resident command provides a
software clock for BW-DOS. When the
correct date and time are entered
(using the DATE and TIME commands),
each file and directory receives the
actual update time.

The clock is based on the VBI
interrupt, so some programs may stop
it. It also does not run during I/O,
which may cause it to drift over time.
It works on both PAL and NTSC systems.

Use ON to install the clock and OFF to
remove it, if it was the last driver
loaded.
